Part 3 – Nàárà Core Engine Technical Architecture

Core Engine Components
Component	Purpose	Interactions
Identity Manager	Unified login/profile/QR	All modules
Activity Tracker	Logs actions for verification & trust	All modules
Trust & Verification Engine	Triangulated trust, anomaly detection	SkillForge, Opportunity Infrastructure, ScamShield
Skill Graph Engine	Stores skill trees and node states	SkillForge, ProofPortfolio, Opportunity Infrastructure
Portfolio Generator	Verifiable outputs (PDF/QR/API)	ProofPortfolio, GlobalGig
Petition Engine	Petition creation, signature tracking	PetitionHub
Resource Engine	FreeCycle & AssetShare	FreeCycle, AssetShare
Notification & Sync Engine	Push, SMS, USSD, offline sync	All modules
Analytics Engine	Aggregated insights for dashboards	Analytics Dashboard, Gov/NGO APIs

Core Engine Data Flow
1.	User action → Activity Tracker logs → Skill/Portfolio update
2.	Trust Layer validates → Updates skill graph/trust score
3.	Portfolio / QR generated → Opportunity Infrastructure triggered
4.	Analytics Engine aggregates metrics → dashboards
5.	Notification Engine alerts users

Trust Algorithm (Simplified MVP)
TrustScore(user) =
0.4 * VerifiedSkillsScore +
0.3 * EvidenceQualityScore +
0.2 * Peer/CustomerRating +
0.1 * ConsistencyScore
Fraud detection:
•	Anomaly flags (mass verification, location mismatch)
•	Cross-module consistency checks

Offline-First Strategy
•	PWA + Service Workers for caching
•	IndexedDB / local storage for offline activity
•	Sync Engine pushes queued actions when connectivity restored
•	USSD/SMS fallback for basic actions

API Overview (MVP)
•	/auth/login – user auth
•	/skills/{user_id} – skill fetch/update
•	/portfolio/{user_id} – fetch/generate portfolio
•	/gigs/search – local/international gig search
•	/freecycle/items – post/claim items
•	/petition/create – create petition
•	/petition/sign/{id} – sign petition
•	/trust/{user_id} – trust score retrieval
•	/analytics/{module} – aggregated metrics for dashboard
Security: OAuth2 tokens, E2E media encryption, consent-based API access


Part 4 – FEMZYK NÀÁRA Full Database Schema & Module Interconnections

1. Database Design Principles
•	Single Source of Truth: All user identity, activity, verification, and content tied to the Identity table.
•	Modular Tables: Each module has its own primary tables linked via user_id or module_id.
•	Offline-First Compatible: Each table stores timestamps and sync flags (is_synced, last_synced).
•	Multi-Source Verification: Tables include verification_source fields for trust scoring.
•	Audit Trail: Every key action is logged in activity_logs for analytics and fraud detection.
•	Scalability: Partitioning by module and region possible for large-scale African deployment.
Recommended Database: PostgreSQL for relational integrity + Supabase/Firebase for real-time sync + optional Redis cache for offline-first PWA responsiveness.

